# Super Admin Features — Walkthrough

## What Was Built

Four super admin feature groups were implemented across 10 files:

### Feature 1: AI Behavior Control
- **Backend**: `AIConfig` singleton model with tone (formal/friendly/technical) and response_length (short/medium/long)
- **APIs**: `GET /api/superadmin/ai-config/` and `POST /api/superadmin/update-ai-config/`
- **Integration**: Chat prompt in `ChatAPIView` now reads `AIConfig.load()` and injects tone/length instructions
- **Frontend**: shadcn `Select` dropdowns with save button, "Current Configuration" display with `Badge` components

### Feature 2: Access Control
- Already enforced via `require_roles(request, {"super_admin"})` on all super admin endpoints
- Regular users and admins get 403 if they try to access these endpoints
- Chat endpoint remains open for all users

### Feature 3: Usage Heatmap
- **API**: `GET /api/superadmin/heatmap/` aggregates from existing `PortfolioEvent` and `ChatMessage` tables
- **Data**: Project views (per project), Section views (projects vs skills), Chatbot usage (last 7 days daily)
- **Frontend**: Animated CSS bar charts with Framer Motion

### Feature 4: System Health
- **API**: `GET /api/superadmin/system-health/` runs live DB check, computes avg response time, uptime
- **Frontend**: Status cards with green/red indicators, stats summary (conversations, messages, uptime)

